-- Corp. Express in deal to buy Lyreco
-- 
-- Wed May 21, 2008 1:14am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/21/us-corporateexpress-lyreco-idUSWEA769320080521

 

 AMSTERDAM  (Reuters) - Dutch office goods supplier Corporate Express CXP.AS said on Wednesday it agreed to buy French rival Lyreco, valuing the company at 1.73 billion euros. 

 Corporate Express, which has been fighting off a hostile takeover from U.S. office goods retailer Staples ( SPLS.O ), said in a statement the deal would increase its 2008 sales and operating profit margin and it would seek shareholders approval. (Reporting by  Gilbert Kreijger )